==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Compete
<hw>Com*pete"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Competed</conjf>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Competing</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[L. <ets>completere</ets>,
<ets>competitum</ets>; <ets>com-</ets> + <ets>petere</ets> to seek. See
<er>Petition</er>.]</ety> <def>To contend emulously; to seek or strive
for the same thing, position, or reward for which another is striving;
to contend in rivalry, as for a prize or in business; <as>as, tradesmen
<ex>compete</ex> with one another</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The rival statesmen, with eyes fixed on America, were all the
while <qex>competing</qex> for European alliances.</q>
<rj><qau>Bancroft.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Competency</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Competence</ent>⟦br⟧
